# ── Local development (two processes) ───────────────────────────────────────
# 1) Start Postgres (and optionally Redis/MinIO):  docker compose up -d postgres
# 2) Copy this file to `.env`, set DATABASE_URL.
# 3) First time or after schema pull:  npm run dev:prepare   (migrate + generate)
# 4) Terminal A:  npm run dev:server   → API on http://127.0.0.1:4002 (see PORT in .env)
# 5) Terminal B:  npm run dev         → UI on http://127.0.0.1:3001 (strict port; proxies /api and /health)
#
# Leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset in dev so the UI uses same-origin `/api/v1` (Vite proxy).
# Optional: if the API runs on a non-default host/port, set the proxy target for Vite only:
# VITE_DEV_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:4002
#
# DATABASE_URL: use host port 5432 with default docker-compose.yml. If Prisma shows a wrong port
# (e.g. 127.0.0.1:59999), clear DATABASE_URL from Windows User/shell environment — dev loads `.env`
# with override so the file wins, but fix stale system vars to avoid confusion.
# Frontend (Vite) — copy to .env or .env.local
# Must include /v1 — do NOT use http://localhost:4002/api alone (causes "API route not found").
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4002/api/v1
# Must match the tenant id used when seeding (`npm run seed` reads VITE_TENANT_ID / E2E_TENANT_ID, else default-tenant-id).
VITE_TENANT_ID=default-tenant-id
# Older seeds used id `default-tenant` — if login fails with valid credentials, try: VITE_TENANT_ID=default-tenant
# Optional: public church site (unauthenticated /website/*) — match Settings → Organization
# VITE_PUBLIC_ORG_NAME=Grace Community Church
# VITE_PUBLIC_ORG_TAGLINE=Rooted in Scripture. Open to all.

# Backend (required in .env for `npm run dev:server`)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/church_erp
# `npm run dev:server` runs `prisma generate` then starts the API (fast). Run `npm run dev:prepare` when migrations changed.
# JWT_SECRET=your-long-random-secret   (optional in dev — a non-production default is applied if unset)
#
# MinIO (optional for local dev — uploads warn if unreachable; docker compose includes MinIO on 9000):
# MINIO_ENDPOINT=localhost
# MINIO_PORT=9000
# MINIO_ACCESS_KEY=admin
# MINIO_SECRET_KEY=password123
#
# Razorpay: test|live; defaults from NODE_ENV (production → live)
# RAZORPAY_MODE=live
# RAZORPAY_RECON_LOOKBACK_SEC=86400
# RAZORPAY_RECON_INTERVAL_MS=21600000
# Post JSON alerts (optional)
# ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=
# BullMQ webhooks; omit to process Razorpay webhooks synchronously
# Docker maps host 6380 → Redis 6379:
# REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6380
# Public webhook: max requests per IP per window
# WEBHOOK_RATE_LIMIT_MAX=300
# WEBHOOK_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
